    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "General Greeting: Hello / Peace be upon you"
        },
        "text": "The most common and formal greeting in Arabic is 'As-salamu alaykum', meaning 'Peace be upon you'. It's used universally across different times of day.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "السلام عليكم",
            "english": "Peace be upon you / Hello",
            "transliteration": "As-salamu alaykum"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "وعليكم السلام",
            "english": "And upon you be peace (Reply)",
            "transliteration": "Wa alaykum as-salam"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Morning Greeting: Good morning"
        },
        "text": "To greet someone in the morning, use 'Sabah al-khayr'. The common reply is 'Sabah an-nur', meaning 'Morning of light'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "صباح الخير",
            "english": "Good morning",
            "transliteration": "Sabah al-khayr"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "صباح النور",
            "english": "Morning of light (Reply)",
            "transliteration": "Sabah an-nur"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Evening Greeting: Good evening"
        },
        "text": "When greeting someone in the evening, you say 'Masa' al-khayr'. The reply is 'Masa' an-nur', similar to the morning greeting.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "مساء الخير",
            "english": "Good evening",
            "transliteration": "Masa' al-khayr"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "مساء النور",
            "english": "Evening of light (Reply)",
            "transliteration": "Masa' an-nur"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
