        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How are you?' (to a male)"
        },
        "text": "To ask a male 'How are you?', you use 'Kayfa haluk?'. Notice the 'ka' sound at the end.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كيف حالكَ؟",
            "english": "How are you? (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Kayfa haluk?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The fatḥa (َ) on the ك indicates a male recipient."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How are you?' (to a female)"
        },
        "text": "To ask a female 'How are you?', you use 'Kayfa haluki?'. Notice the 'ki' sound at the end, indicated by the kasra.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كيف حالكِ؟",
            "english": "How are you? (to a female)",
            "transliteration": "Kayfa haluki?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The kasra (ِ) on the ك indicates a female recipient."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
